[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is the Uvi M8 E1 UV printer. It\'s an insanely awesome budget-friendly UV printer so us smaller creators can get in on the UV printing game and harness some truly epic technology. For decades UV printers were confined to industrial'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'settings costing tens of thousands of dollars. They were bulky and too complex for everyday users until now. I\'ve had this printer in my studio for the past 9 months ever since that first video I did with Uvi M8 and we love it. We used it a'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ton making prototype cards for that TCG I designed. It was so nice to be able to make a design and then instantly print it out onto a playing card and see what it would look like in real life. Plus'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you all seem to really enjoy that last video we made where we took thrift store junk and turned it into profitable art with this UV printer. That\'s why I\'m super hyped Uvi M8 reached back out to me and said, "1000 bro, we need a'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sequel. You\'ve barely scratched the surface on turning thrift store junk into treasures." And I said, "Okay, bye." Didn\'t quite go like that but we\'re back baby. So shout out to Uvi M8'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for coming back and sponsoring this video. I\'m excited. This thing can print in 2D, it can even print in 3D like raised ink printing. It can print on ceramic, metal, wood, just a ton of different surfaces. And with the rotary'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'attachment you can print on curved surfaces like mugs and tumblers. Set up is super easy. You just kind of pop in the ink, download the app and then the printer does everything else automatically. Okay, so Nick, come here'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'buddy. We\'re back at it again. It\'s a UVquel. All right, so you and I are both going to go to thrift stores. We\'re going to get some junk. We\'re going to turn it into beautiful masterpieces that we sell'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for profit with this machine. But this time we\'re going to do things a little bit differently. Last time our budget was $30, this time our budget is $60. And you can buy as much stuff as you want but the final collection that we\'re'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going to present is just three items. &gt;&gt; So, you can print five, six, 20 items, and then narrow it down to your favorite three. &gt;&gt; And last time we did like, you know, whoever sells it for the most wins, but'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
