VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'my lovely boys, Nick gave me a crash course in Photoshop so I could remove the background of the picture to make stickers. And after a little Googling of Photoshop controls cuz I\'m no pro, my stickers were ready to go. &gt;&gt; My wife and I have been rewatching Attack on Titan recently, and as soon as'

[10:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I heard we were doing this again, I thought of a perfect idea to kind of show off the 3D aspects of the printer. What I would be doing is this, where the Titan\'s face is in the wall. And this would be like one layer of plywood, and'

[11:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then this would be a second layer of plywood. I started my interpretation by roughly tracing the original piece. Then I fumbled around with some watercolor brushes until I got a gradient that somewhat matched the original image. I'

[11:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'noticed that my wall had a lot less texture than the original, so I found some pictures of walls and bricks online and made a texture out of them in Photoshop using the threshold filter. After bringing those back in on top of my sketch, I went through with a vector'

[11:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'brush to fill in the important lines. Then I colored in the Titan\'s face and my drawing was ready to print. On my saw, these screws are really old and a bit bent. I tried a few methods to get them out and with a bit of work I'

[11:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'finally got them. Even with the screws out, the handle was kind of rusted to the blade or I don\'t know, it was gunked up in there and it was tough to get off. Plus I couldn\'t get a good grip on the blade without'

[11:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'just ripping my hand into the saw teeth. But I did eventually get it separated. I took a picture of the blade and brought that into my iPad with this tiger character I drew. Once I got the art in place, I started adding these yellow green moon waves to flesh out the'

[12:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'composition and fill up more space on the blade. The blade had a thicker piece of metal on one side so I used a couple of very thin rulers to level it out for the printer. After the printer took a snapshot of the blade, I brought my art'

[12:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in and got it in the spot I wanted it to be. I think doing the art placement on this printer is super simple and I can usually get everything lined up in just a couple of minutes. All in all, the software is pretty easy to use. Then I hit print and the printer went off and'

[12:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
