[17:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the edges, placed it on the printer, lined everything up in the UV Make Studio, then I used the relief texture feature to give the wall some 3D texture. Then, I hit print. In order to save some time and ink on this print, I'

[18:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'erased the face from the top print, since I\'m going to print this again later on the back piece. All right, I need to paint the sides now. I really should have done that first, so I\'ll spray the edges and go'

[18:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from there. &gt;&gt; Okay, so listen, I was just going to like cancel this for my whole project, but then I remembered this thing can print onto an adhesive surface, and then you kind of laminate that, and then you'

[18:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can I\'m hesitant to call it a sticker. It\'s kind of like a sticker. Ooh, my print\'s done. Uh it\'s kind of like a sticker, but you literally like press the full UV print onto the surface and then peel the backing away, and'

[18:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there\'s not like, you know, some die-cut sticker-looking thing. It\'s just like literally a super durable UV print pressed onto the object. So, even though this thing is too tall for the printer, I think I can still make this work by doing that adhesive printing.'

[19:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I took a picture of the oil can and brought it into my iPad to start working on the design. A lot of these little mini projects, I\'ve been taking some of my existing art and just kind of putting them on cool objects, and that\'s one of'

[19:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the strengths of this printer. If you\'re an artist, you can take stuff you\'ve already done, and with the U F Me E1, turn it into merch or turn it into prints or something that you can sell. But, you know, I had to make at least one fully original piece of art for this'

[19:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video. I had to do it to them. So, what better to put on my oil can than an oil can? Technically, this can is for hydraulic brake fluid, but we don\'t need to worry about that. It\'s an oil can.'

[19:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This artwork is definitely giving some Cuphead vibes. That was certainly an influence, and then in and of itself, Cuphead is heavily influenced by all kinds of vintage cartoons from, what is it? The \'40s? The \'30s? Old cartoons. So, I\'m definitely leaning into that'

[19:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'vibe, and I think this is going to turn out cool. I loaded this decal paper into the printer and peeled back the protective plastic. The printer started printing, and my graphics turned out really good. Now, this laminator, this is the laminator they sent us on the'

[20:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'last video, and it was an early prototype unit. I think something\'s wrong with ours cuz like the only way to get the paper to go through is continuously open and close the lid over and over again, which forces the machine to feed the paper through like a half an'

[20:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'inch at a time. I scraped down my graphic to make sure it was really adhered to the sticky stuff, then I cut out my graphic pretty close to the design and slowly peeled off the backing. I carefully placed my graphic'

